leg-rope
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:2
Definition:to tie a back-leg of a bailed cow at milking to prevent it kicking the bucket.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (mainly dairy farming)
